name: FirstBaseline

properties.name: ASCENT_OFFSET
properties.description: The tallest character in the font falls below the top inset of the object.

properties.name: CAP_HEIGHT
properties.description: The tops of upper case letters touch the top inset of the object.

properties.name: LEADING_OFFSET
properties.description: The text leading value defines the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.

properties.name: EMBOX_HEIGHT
properties.description: The text em box height is the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.

properties.name: X_HEIGHT
properties.description: The tops of lower case letters touch the top inset of the object.

properties.name: FIXED_HEIGHT
properties.description: Uses the value specified for minimum first baseline offset as the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.

description: Starting point options for the first baseline of text.
